snippet.textDisplay:
More fun facts about AZ-1:
1. Its brother, Suzuki Cappuccino was dyno-ed and a 63-64ps figure was obtained AT THE WHEELS (so maybe closer to 80ps at crank. this is similar to the case of 280ps JDMs where some of them actually has more horsepower than that). You can expect around same horsepower in AZ-1 which has same engine.
2. Cappuccino was raced in Japan's famous Best Motoring program against the old MX-5 at the time (~115-130ps) and they had very close lap time in Tsukuba, while AZ-1 handily beat the cappuccino on the same track in the same program by few seconds thanks to much better handling.
So basically AZ-1 is considerably faster than MX-5 back at the time on a proper race track (at least when without long straights). That's amazing even when considering the lying AZ-1 power figure.
